other_tests.findings: The liver is diffusely hypoattenuating, compatible with hepatic steatosis. The gallbladder contains at least one radiopaque gallstone in the neck and is mildly distended. A tubular, fluid-filled and rim-enhancing structure in the right lower quadrant is consistent with dilation of the appendiceal tip. No free air or ascites is present. The stomach and intra-abdominal loops of bowel are normal.
